        OS and data. Every OSD needs to have minimum three disks. However, in general each OSD nodes
        will have three sets of disks based on usages:</p><ol id="ol_qpr_jnb_lt" class="- topic/ol " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\ceph\configuration_files.dita" xtrc="ol:1;360:82">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\ceph\configuration_files.dita" xtrc="li:12;361:13">Systems disks used for OS, logging etc.<!-- Minimum count it 2--></li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\ceph\configuration_files.dita" xtrc="li:13;362:13">Data disks. Minimum count is 1</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\ceph\configuration_files.dita" xtrc="li:14;363:13">Journal disks. Minimum count is 0. If you do not configure journal disks for a disks
          then a partition of data disk is used as journal disk.</li>
      </ol><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\ceph\configuration_files.dita" xtrc="p:16;365:15">Sets of OSD disks are mapped to journal disks. The below example illustrates the above
